reviews.text:
Tom Yam Yong Tau Foo the gravy and the home make chilli sauce is super nice . Coffee is grind from coffee seed on the spot and half boil eggs is big and fresh , waffle is nice .
Atmosphere is cool and relaxing with free wifi . Staff is friendly and courtesy.
Will come back again.

The Claypot Sesame Chicken was amazing it tasted so homely! Staff service was excellent as well , definitely a hidden gem tucked away in a small neighborhood of Tampines. The prices were affordable, ranging from $5 to $8 as well

Ordered french toast, half boiled egg, beancurd pudding and curry mee. Curry mee is good with generous amount of tender chicken albeit abit pricy (similar to those in shopping mall cafe). There are small pcs of chilli paddy inside the curry so remove it if can't take it too spicy. Photo shown is half eaten. French toast is rather small pc for the price and taste so so.

Halal certified. Aircon place with plenty of parking space nearby. Good option to have in a neighbourhood to escape the heat when hungry. As others said, the femalr service crew service was very good and pleasant.

An unassuming eatery situated outside the brahm centre.

Service by the two ladies were top notch! They are very friendly, greeting us with smiles and were extremely attentive.

Ordered the chicken tofu clay pot rice ($8) and enjoyed it. Will be back again to try the other dishes
